This issue is not only for JIRA; it's for all products.  The website icons all have a white background but they would be prettier with a transparent background.  I attached a screenshot of my Windows 7 taskbar showing the Atlassian icons next to a number of other icons.  The Atlassian icons on the taskbar are from adding application shortcuts via Google Chrome.

Here are the steps to reproduce this bug:
# Create 2 new projects (Project A & Project B)
# Create a URL custom field type and set it applicable only to Project B
# Create a new issue in Project A (e.g: PRA-1)
# Click on 'Move this issue' operation
# Select on Project B and any issue types
# Fill in a long URL that exceeds its max char length *255* - http://test.website.com/?test1=1&
# Click on 'Move' button in Step 4 of 4
# You will hit into the following error:
{noformat}
com.atlassian.jira.exception.DataAccessException: org.ofbiz.core.entity.GenericEntityException: while inserting: [GenericEntity:CustomFieldValue][id,10001][stringvalue,http://test.website.com/?test1=1&][issue,10001][parentkey,null][customfield,10000] (SQL Exception while executing the following:INSERT INTO customfieldvalue (ID, ISSUE, CUSTOMFIELD, PARENTKEY, STRINGVALUE, NUMBERVALUE, TEXTVALUE, DATEVALUE, VALUETYPE) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?) (Data truncation: Data too long for column 'STRINGVALUE' at row 1))
{noformat}
# Go back to the Issue navigator and do a search for Project A
# Click on PRA-1 issue key and you will be seeing "ISSUE DOES NOT EXIST":
{noformat}
Error

The issue you are trying to view does not exist. 
{noformat}
# Try to search for Project B and you will find no issues were shown
# Looking inside the database and doing a select query for project A, the issue is not there anymore:
{noformat}
select * from jiraissue where pkey='PRA-1';
{noformat}
# But, doing a select query for project B, the issue will be shown:
{noformat}
select * from jiraissue where pkey='PRB-1';
{noformat}

Well, the problem would be solved after running a full *re-index* via _Administration -> System -> Indexing_ but this is definitely a bug. 

The reason is because since the move process have been interrupted with the "Data truncation" error, the issue should not be moved to another project and thus, delete off the old issue.

