It would be nice if the requests to get the header images had "png" in their extension. For example, to get the drowpdown arrow we call

{code}
GET /rest/api/1.0/dropdowns?color=ffffff&bgcolor=114070 HTTP/1.1
{code}

It would be better if we call:

{code}
GET /rest/api/1.0/dropdowns.png?color=ffffff&bgcolor=114070 HTTP/1.1
{code}

This would allow browsers to see that this request serves only PNGs. Some browsers could then ignore the request for the image, for example, if they had images turned off completely.

Regards,
Brenden.

