Currently the intro gadget has a "Create your first project" link. However, if there is no assignable user, the project lead field cannot do autocompletion. Even if you enter the admin's userid directly, you'll still get warning of "User not assignable" and you cannot create issue because of this problem.

So it may be logical to add an "Add new user" (and perhaps "Add new group") link to the intro gadget in this case?

There may be a step in the final stage of setting up JIRA to allow you to add users. However, for hosted JIRA and Studio, the admin does not perform the installation and setting up JIRA. For their first step after logging into a new instance of Hosted JIRA or Studio is to create users.
